node.text: Omg y’all.....add this to the list of crazy things we used to do before Rona! This was exactly 1 year ago and little did I know I was documenting the very last time I went out grocery shopping with both kids 😂😂 Let’s just say I didn’t need a pandemic to tell me not to do that again!

node.text:
So I got up this morning to get the kids ready and realized I forgot to buy milk last night 😱 Then I remembered the instant porridges that the lovely team at @gracefoods gave to me and I thought well they can eat this! It was their first time trying it and they loved it! You know I always make porridge for them so if they liked this, then it must be really good! Definitely adding this to my list of quick breakfasts for those school mornings when I’m short on time! .

node.text:
Coconut milk in the tin: I have about 5 at any given time stocked in my pantry. But have you ever had someone make you rice & peas with freshly made coconut milk? That’s love right there🤎 I choose the right coconut by shaking it and holding it to my ear. If you can hear the juice inside swishing back and forth then it’s a good one! Use a hammer to loosen the shell, use your hand or sometimes a knife to loosen the meat from the shell, chop it up, and blend it with water. Not too much water though! It’ll be too watery! I remove as much water as I can from the peas when it’s done cooking and set it aside. Then add in the coconut milk. You should yield about 2 cups of coconut milk. Boil the peas in coconut milk and a cup of that water you set aside from the peas & then add rice! Voila! Rice name shelly! 😂 I used parboiled rice this time. There’s a tutorial on my YouTube channel that goes deeper into detail so make sure you subscribe! Type in the search: thatnursecancook rice and peas if you have trouble finding it! 
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
I love this song’s message. Black is beauty! Honor black women 🤎 Happy Sunday y’all. I’ll call this dish “1,2,3” because Jamaican women have been killing track & field 🔥 Today it’s stew chicken, rice & peas with freshly made coconut milk from scratch, steamed vegetables, and baked mac & cheese! 
.
.
.
.
Subscribe to my 🎥YouTube channel (thatnursecancook) recipes are there! Just type thatnursecancook and the dish you’re looking for into the search  if you can’t find it! 
.
.
.
.

node.text:
Confession: everytime I make jerk shrimp I eat like 2 or 3 when they come out of the pan 😂 This time it was Jerk Shrimp with Creamy Cheese Ravioli. I elevated the recipe by adding a little pepper jack cheese & mozzarella to the cream sauce. This was sooo good. If you already have the “Dinner in 30” ebook, save the reel I just posted to use as a reference! Recipe inside “Dinner in 30” ebook available for immediate download at shopthatnursecancook.com (link in bio)
.

.

node.text: I posted another pic of this in my IG story last week and I promised that I’d make it again. Jerk Shrimp with Creamy Cheese Ravioli. I made a slight adjustment and cooked the jerk shrimp first. Use the same pan to make both! The leftover seasonings from the jerk shrimp really add depth to the flavor and this time i sprinkled just a bit of pepper jack cheese and mozzarella into the cream sauce. Omg. This was soo good and best of all it’s ready in 30 minutes! Recipe is inside my ebook “Dinner in 30” available for immediate download at shopthatnursecancook.com (link in bio)

node.text:
I love a rich and hearty beef stew. Loaded with onions, peppers, carrots, and potatoes...it’s a whole bashment in your belly. Forreal. This recipe is 🔥🔥 I made it with some yellow rice and peas, fried plantain, with some pear and tomato on the side. Don’t forget a nice pineapple ginger beer to wash it down😉 Who’s coming over for dinner? 
.
.
.
.
👉🏾Subscribe to my 🎥YouTube channel. Recipe is LIVE! Link in my bio! The recipe for the rice is there too. Just type it into the search bar: thatnursecancook yellow rice and peas if you can’t find it! Thanks to all my subscribers!
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
Is it stew beef or is it beef stew? Doesn’t really matter as long as the flavor’s there, right? I used chuck beef stew, seasoned it up, and “brown stewed” it by burning the sugar first. It’s a totally different flavor profile compared to simply stewing it in the pot alone. I intended to make coconut yellow rice & peas but ran out of coconut milk so I remixed the recipe a lil and just omitted the milk; used water instead! This was soooo nice and tender! Melt in your mouth!
.
.
.
.
🔥Recipe now LIVE! On my 🎥YouTube channel! The rice and peas recipe is there too! Subscribe to the link in my bio! Type in the search: thatnursecancook yellow rice and peas if you’re having trouble finding it
.
.
.
.
.

node.text: Crispy Baked Parmesan Chicken! Let me tell it. Spatchcock your chicken: it cooks more evenly and faster. Drop it in a cast iron skillet ‘cuz it conducts heat like a dream. Grind up those fresh herbs and make sure you get under the skin. Bake that bird and give her a nice parmesan butta bath. Put it back in the oven and let that skin get crispy and you’ve got the best Baked Parmesan Chicken you’ll ever taste in your life. You can take my word for it or you can see for yourself! Full recipe on thatnursecooks.com (link in bio) 😉

node.text:
This is how I get ready for bed sometimes! Have you been feeling a bit under the weather? Or just need to support your immune system in the coming months? Try this tea! Not gonna lie. It will make you very sleepy and drowsy so be sure you don’t have to drive or operate machinery or have kids to take care of! I swear half a cup of this had me feeling like I took 5 melatonin gummies 😂
.
.
👉🏾👉🏾What’s in it?
⭐️5 cups of water
⭐️4 slices of orange 
⭐️4 slices of lime
⭐️4 dried Eucalyptus leaves
⭐️1 large piece of ginger cut up
⭐️2 handfuls of Chamomile flowers
⭐️1 tsp Organic powdered Turmeric
⭐️2-3 drops of Angosturra Bitters
👉🏾👉🏾Sweeten it with your choice of sweetener(Honey, Agave, Sugar, etc)
👉🏾Add the ingredients to boiling water. Once all of your ingredients are in, boil on a high flame for 15 minutes
.
.
.
